{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770137725,"nonce":"PhC/gmhfOvzOA50C14jRbyI7UMY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n_pCs","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/148","origin":"github"},"title":"Fix critical bugs in revert_feature.sh","message":"## Summary\n\nFix critical bugs identified in `.agent/scripts/revert_feature.sh` during PR #146 review.\n\n## Parent Issue\n\nSub-issue of #139\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe revert script has several bugs that could cause failed reverts to appear successful:\n\n### Bug 1: Subshell Exit Code Not Propagated\n```bash\n# Lines 127-158: The pipe creates a subshell\ngit log ... | tac | while read commit; do\n    ...\n    exit 1  # This only exits the subshell!\ndone\n\nif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then  # Always true - checks loop exit, not revert status\n```\n**Impact**: Failed reverts will appear successful, potentially leading to pushing incomplete reverts.\n\n### Bug 2: Missing pipefail\n```bash\nset -e  # Doesn't catch pipe failures\n# Should be:\nset -e\nset -o pipefail\n```\n\n### Bug 3: Unused Variables\n```bash\nREVERTED=0  # Incremented inside subshell - lost when subshell exits\nFAILED=0    # Never used\n```\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nRestructure using process substitution or mapfile to avoid subshell:\n```bash\nset -e\nset -o pipefail\n\n# Store commits in array (avoids subshell)\nmapfile -t COMMITS \u003c \u003c(git log --all --grep=\"#$ISSUE\" --format=%H --reverse | tac)\n\nREVERTED=0\nfor commit in \"${COMMITS[@]}\"; do\n    # ... revert logic\n    ((REVERTED++))\ndone\n\necho \"Successfully reverted $REVERTED commits\"\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Add `set -o pipefail` to script header\n- [ ] Restructure revert loop to avoid subshell (use mapfile or temp file)\n- [ ] Fix or remove REVERTED/FAILED counters\n- [ ] Add test coverage in `.agent/scripts/tests/test_revert_feature.sh`\n  - [ ] Test argument parsing (--issue, --dry-run, --help)\n  - [ ] Test issue number validation\n  - [ ] Test dry-run mode behavior\n  - [ ] Test error handling for non-existent issues\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Script correctly exits with error on revert failure\n- [ ] Script correctly reports success only when all reverts complete\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] Dry-run mode accurately previews what will happen\n\n## Effort Estimate\n\n**Small** (1-2 hours)\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Opus 4.5`","files":null}]}